Hey doc,<br><br>
It's not a good thing for you to refer to confidential, anonymous email communications between you and vets who purportedly &quot;don't like&quot; Cook. You put yourself in a position as being their proxy. I don't suspect that Cook pays it much heed, but still it comes across as a &quot;low bridge&quot; tactic.<br><br>
Another thing, I don't recall Cook ever calling you or Marc Weiss anything derogatory in regards to being Jewish. Don't put  bad words in his mouth. He is quite capable of doing that himself - such as his reference to you as being homosexual.<br><br>
As for myself, I agree with a few things Cook says. Not many, but a few. He comes across, first and foremost, as a person who failed to be recognized for what he feels was righteous, honorable, and noble - his service in Vietnam. This is very important to him. I respect that and feel that he should be able to express himself as he sees fit. If you look closely you will see beneath the coarse exterior, a fragile human being.<br><br>

